definitions.definition: Administration ; the use of limited resources combined with forecasting, planning, leadership and execution skills to achieve predetermined specific goals.
The executives of an organisation, especially senior executives .
Judicious use of means to accomplish an end.
examples: Excellent time management helped her succeed in all facets of her life.
